# BeeRad LLC - Email Configuration

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your email credentials.

```bash
cp .env.local.example .env.local
```

## Variables

```env
# Gmail address used to send contact form notifications
EMAIL_USER=your-gmail@gmail.com

# Gmail App Password (NOT your regular Gmail password)
# Generate at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# (Requires 2-Step Verification to be enabled on your Google account)
EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password-here

# Email address where contact form submissions are delivered
# Defaults to EMAIL_USER if not set
EMAIL_TO=contact@beeradllc.com
```

## How to Get a Gmail App Password

1. Go to your Google Account settings at https://myaccount.google.com
2. Select **Security** → **2-Step Verification** (enable it if not already on)
3. Under 2-Step Verification, scroll down and select **App passwords**
4. Choose **Mail** as the app and **Other** as the device, give it a name (e.g. "BeeRad Website")
5. Copy the generated 16-character password and paste it as `EMAIL_PASS`

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to version control (it is in `.gitignore`)
- Use a dedicated Gmail account for sending if possible
- Rotate the app password periodically
